9. Display the top 10 order IDs along with total units for those orders [10 rows].
10. Display the list of products in the “Condiments” category [12 rows].
11. Select all employees with their full names who were 40 years old or older at the time of hiring [3 rows].
12. Display a list with customer contact names and their addresses, provided they have placed orders shipped via “Speedy Express” [249 rows].
13. Display the list of customers who have not made any purchases [4 rows].
14. Display a list of products along with total units in stock, where the quantity is greater than 100. Name the total field “TotalUnits” [10 rows].
15. Display a list of employees and customers involved in orders shipped to Brussels via “Speedy Express” [2 rows].
16. Select job titles and full names of employees who have sold at least one unit of “Queso Cabrales” or “Tofu” [9 rows].
17. List the full names of employees and the last name of their managers (consider null values for those who don’t report to anyone) [9 rows].
18. Select distinct contact names of customers, product names, and supplier company names, for all customers living in London and for all suppliers whose company name is "Karkki Oy" or "Pavlova, Ltd." [9 rows].
19. From all orders involving employees and customers from multiple cities, select product names where either the customer or employee is from London [76 rows].
20. Display a list of all customers who have purchased products with a unit price lower than 3 [26 rows].
21. Select full names of employees who have worked longer than any employee residing in London (who have more seniority than the most senior London-based employee). Use the CURRENT_DATE function to calculate seniority [4 rows].
22. Display a list of full names and city of employees who have sold to customers from the same city [6 rows].
23. Display the average price per category [8 rows].
24. Display a list of company names that supply more than 4 products [2 rows].
25. Display a list of employee IDs, their full names, and the number of distinct products they have sold. Sort ascending by employee ID [9 rows].
26. Display a list of employee IDs, their full names, and the total revenue generated by each. Sort ascending by employee ID [9 rows].
27. Display the top 5 shipping cities by revenue [5 rows].
28. Display the top 5 products by units sold [5 rows].
29. Display a list of distinct customers who have purchased products in the “Beverages” category [83 rows].
30. Rank suppliers by number of distinct products sold [29 rows].
31. How many orders were placed in June 1997?
32. What was the day with the highest number of orders in 1998?
33. Which employee ID had the highest sales?
34. Which shipping country generated the most revenue from Freight?
35. Calculate total sales grouped by year. Present in both table and column chart format.
36. Calculate total sales grouped by month for the year 1997. Present in table and line chart format.
37. Calculate total sales grouped by year for the “Condiments” category. Present in table and bar chart format.
38. Show how many orders were shipped by Speedy Express, United Package, and Federal Shipping. Present in table and pie chart format. 
39. Show monthly revenue for 1997 comparing “Beverages” and “Confections”. Each row represents a month, each column a category. Present in table and line chart format.*/
